==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sulphureous
<hw>Sul*phu"re*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sulphureus</ets>, <ets>sulfureus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Consisting of
sulphur; having the qualities of sulphur, or brimstone; impregnated with
sulphur.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her snakes united, <qex>sulphureous</qex> waters drink.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sul*phu"re*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sul*phu"re*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sulphuret</ent>⟦br⟧
